Third-party software distributed with MetaEdit
================================================

ExifTool
--------
MetaEdit bundles ExifTool by Phil Harvey as an external subprocess for all
metadata reads and writes. ExifTool is not linked against MetaEdit's code;
it is redistributed as-is inside the application bundle.

- Version: pinned in Scripts/fetch-exiftool.sh (currently 13.58)
- Source:  https://github.com/exiftool/exiftool
- Website: https://exiftool.org
- License: ExifTool is free software; you can redistribute it and/or modify
  it under the same terms as Perl itself — i.e. dual-licensed under the
  Artistic License and the GNU General Public License.

The full license text ships alongside the bundled copy: the fetch script
places ExifTool's LICENSE and README files in Tools/exiftool/, and the build
copies them into MetaEdit.app/Contents/Resources/exiftool/ next to the
exiftool script itself.

Before each public release, re-check the LICENSE file of the pinned ExifTool
version for changes.
